  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 3:8-10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 3:8-10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Fine gold amounting to six hundred talents — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, upward of three millions forty-five thousand pounds sterling. This vast sum was expended on the holy of holies alone, a room only ten yards square. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The weight of the nails — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, of each of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "nails, screws, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "pins, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "by which the golden plates were fastened to the walls that were overlaid with them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was fifty shekels of gold — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The meaning seems to be, that each ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "weighed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was worth ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that sum, workmanship and all. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Two cherubims of image-work — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, sculpture-work. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And overlaid them with gold — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For they were made of olive-wood, and were not, like those of Moses, of beaten gold. Nor were they fixed, as his were, to the mercy-seat, but appeared in a moving posture.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
